{"title_page": "Maryana Naumova", "text_new": "{{Expand Russian|topic=bio|\u041d\u0430\u0443\u043c\u043e\u0432\u0430, \u041c\u0430\u0440\u044c\u044f\u043d\u0430 \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0430|date=November 2014}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Maryana Naumova\n| image       = \u041d\u0430\u0443\u043c\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u041c\u0430\u0440\u044c\u044f\u043d\u0430, \u043d\u0430\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043d\u0430 \u0442\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0438\u0440\u0435 \u0410\u0440\u043d\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0434 \u041a\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0441\u0438\u043a.jpg\n| image_size  =\n| caption     =  Naumova at the 2013 [[Arnold Classic]]\n| other_names = \n| birth_name  = Maryana Aleksandrovna Naumova\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1999|4|22|}}\n| death_date  = \n| residence   = \n| nationality = [[Russian people|Russian]]\n| known_for   = \n| employer    = \n| occupation  = \n| height      = \n| weight      = \n}}\n'''Maryana Aleksandrovna Naumova''' ({{lang-ru|\u041c\u0430\u0440\u0438\u0430\u0301\u043d\u0430 \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u0301\u043d\u0434\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0430 \u041d\u0430\u0443\u0301\u043c\u043e\u0432\u0430}}; born 22 April 1999 in [[Staraya Russa]]) is a [[Russia]]n [[powerlifting|powerlifter]], who specializes in [[bench press]], and was the leading teenage girl in the world in the discipline. She has won multiple world championships, has set over 15 world records<!-- in the bench press--> in her age category and holds the title of [[Master of Sport of Russia|Master of Sport of Russia, International Class]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://mstrok.ru/?id=1947|script-title=ru:\u0421\u0430\u043c\u0430\u044f \u0441\u0438\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0434\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0447\u043a\u0430 \u043f\u043b\u0430\u043d\u0435\u0442\u044b \u043f\u043e\u0441\u0435\u0442\u0438\u043b\u0430 \u041d\u0438\u0436\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u0422\u0430\u0433\u0438\u043b|publisher=News agency \"Mezhdu Strok\"|date=2013-11-05|language=Russian|accessdate=2014-10-23}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nMaryana Naumova is the first female under-18 to be allowed to participate in professional powerlifting tournaments.<ref name=\"aif.ru 2015-03-09\" /> In March 2015 she participated in the [[Arnold Classic]], establishing the female record in the event Arnold BenchBach, lifting 150&nbsp;kg (331&nbsp;lbs). After the tournament she asked [[Arnold Schwarzenegger]] to become the [[President of the United States]] and normalize [[Russia\u2013United States relations]]. She also passed Arnold letters from [[Donbass]] children.<ref name=\"aif.ru 2015-03-09\">{{cite news|title=\u0428\u043a\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0430 \u0438\u0437 \u041f\u043e\u0434\u043c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u044c\u044f \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0430\u043b\u0430 \u0428\u0432\u0430\u0440\u0446\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0433\u0433\u0435\u0440\u0443 \u043f\u0438\u0441\u044c\u043c\u0430 \u043e\u0442 \u0434\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0439 \u0414\u043e\u043d\u0431\u0430\u0441\u0441\u0430|url=http://www.aif.ru/sport/other/1462834|agency=[[Argumenty i Fakty]]|date=9 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=\u0421\u0430\u043c\u0430\u044f \u0441\u0438\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0434\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0447\u043a\u0430 \u0432 \u043c\u0438\u0440\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0438\u043b\u0430 \u0428\u0432\u0430\u0440\u0446\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0433\u0433\u0435\u0440\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u043c\u0438\u0440\u0438\u0442\u044c \u0421\u0428\u0410 \u0438 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u044e|url=http://lenta.ru/news/2015/03/09/naumova/|agency=[[Lenta.ru|Lenta]]|date=9 March 2015}}</ref>\n\nAs part of [[Russia's role in the Syrian Civil War|Russia's support]] for the Assad government during the [[Syrian Civil War]], Naumova was sent to Damascus at the invitation of [[Asma al-Assad]], the president\u2019s wife.<ref>{{cite news|title=Syria: Positions harden|url=https://www.economist.com/news/middle-east-and-africa/21664155-hopes-diplomatic-progress-aimed-ending-war-go-reverse-positions|accessdate=12 September 2015|work=[[The Economist]]|date=12 September 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn commemoration of the late Russian revolutionary [[Vladimir Lenin]], Naumova had joined the [[Communist Party of the Russian Federation]] to celebrate Lenin's 146th birthday and lay flowers at the Mausoleum on Red Square. Naumova was awarded the Order of the UCP-CPSU - also known as \"Friendship of the People\" - for her humanitarian aid work throughout the world. Professional MMA fighter [[Jeff Monson]] had also joined Naumova and the Communist Party to celebrate the life and legacy of Lenin.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u0413.\u0410. \u0417\u044e\u0433\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432: \u041d\u0430 \u043f\u043b\u0430\u043d\u0435\u0442\u0435 \u043d\u0435\u043c\u0430\u043b\u043e \u0438\u0437\u0432\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043b\u044e\u0434\u0435\u0439, \u043d\u043e \u043d\u0435\u043c\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0433\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435\u0432|url=https://kprf.ru/party-live/cknews/154216.html|work=KPRF|date=22 April 2016|language=Russian}}</ref>\n\nAt the 2016 Arnolds Sports Festival she participated in the SSP Nutrition Pro Raw Bench competition. She lifted 110&nbsp;kg and placed 3rd, but was later disqualified due to a positive doping test and suspended from lifting for two years.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.powerlifting-ipf.com/fileadmin/ipf/data/anti-doping/IPF_current_ADRV-list_2016_06_16.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-08-03 |url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160917053950/http://www.powerlifting-ipf.com/fileadmin/ipf/data/anti-doping/IPF_current_ADRV-list_2016_06_16.pdf |archivedate=2016-09-17 |df= }}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n===Inline citations===\n{{reflist}}\n\n===General references===\n: <small>{{cite news|url=http://ria.ru/video/20100315/214343203.html|script-title=ru:\u0414\u0435\u0441\u044f\u0442\u0438\u043b\u0435\u0442\u043d\u044f\u044f \u0434\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0447\u043a\u0430 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0442 \u0440\u0435\u043a\u043e\u0440\u0434\u044b |publisher=[[RIA Novosti]]|date=2010-03-15|language=Russian|accessdate=2014-10-23}}<br />{{cite news|url=http://rt.com/sport/powerlifting-maryana-naumova-guinness-record-765-881/|title=Girl raises bar on Guinness powerlifting record|publisher=[[Russia Today]]|date=2011-09-06|accessdate=2014-10-23}}<br />{{cite news|url=http://en.ria.ru/video/20110929/167248224.html|title=Russia\u2019s strongest girl yells at barbell to win|publisher=[[RIA Novosti]]|date=2011-09-29|language=Russian|accessdate=2014-10-23}}<br />{{cite news|url=http://en.ria.ru/video/20111117/168777676.html|title=Russian schoolgirl breaks world powerlifting record|publisher=[[RIA Novosti]]|date=2011-11-17|accessdate=2014-10-23}}<br />{{cite web|url=http://www.muscleandfitness.com/athletes-celebrities/news/maryana-naumova-tiniest-champ|title=Maryana Naumova - The Tiniest Champ|publisher=Muscle & Fitness|year=2012|accessdate=2014-10-23}}<br />{{cite news|url=http://english.pravda.ru/news/sports/06-03-2013/123987-arnold_classic-0|title=Russian girl wins Arnold Classic on bench barbell press|publisher=Pravda.Ru|date=2013-03-06|accessdate=2014-10-23}}<br />{{cite news|url=http://en.ria.ru/world/20130307/179863330/Russian-Schoolgirl-Sets-World-Record-in-Power-Lifting.html|title=Russian Schoolgirl Sets World Record in Power Lifting|publisher=[[RIA Novosti]]|date=2013-03-07|accessdate=2014-10-23}}<br />{{cite news|url=http://dni.ru/sport/2013/3/6/249316.html|script-title=ru:\u042e\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0440\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u044f\u043d\u043a\u0430 \u0448\u043e\u043a\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0430 \u0428\u0432\u0430\u0440\u0446\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0433\u0433\u0435\u0440\u0430|publisher=Dni.Ru|date=2013-03-06|language=Russian|accessdate=2014-10-23}}<br />{{cite news|url=http://www.aif.ru/sport/other/1343063|script-title=ru:15-\u043b\u0435\u0442\u043d\u044f\u044f \u0440\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u044f\u043d\u043a\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0434\u043d\u044f\u043b\u0430 \u0448\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0433\u0443 \u0432\u0435\u0441\u043e\u043c 145 \u043a\u0438\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043c\u043c\u043e\u0432|publisher=[[Argumenty i Facty]]|language=Russian|date=2014-09-22|accessdate=2014-10-23}}<br />{{cite news|url=http://spor.mynet.com/diger-sporlar/70065-15-yasinda-inanilmazi-basardi.html|title=15 ya\u015f\u0131nda inan\u0131lmaz\u0131 ba\u015fard\u0131|publisher=Spor Mynet|language=Turkish|date=2014-09-24|accessdate=2014-10-23}}<br />{{cite news|url=https://uk.eurosport.yahoo.com/blogs/world-of-sport/what-this-15-year-old-girl-can-do-is-just-scary-144212693.html|title=What this 15-year-old girl can do is just scary|author=[[Eurosport]]|publisher=[[Yahoo! News|Yahoo! Sport]]|date=2014-10-08|accessdate=2014-10-23}}</small>\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Maryana Naumova}}\n* [http://en.allpowerlifting.com/lifters/RUS/naumova-maryana-30848/ Maryana Naumova record] at Allpowerlifting.com\n* [http://mhpstrong.com/tag/maryana-naumova/ News on Maryana Naumova] at MHP\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Naumova, Maryana}}\n[[Category:1999 births]]\n[[Category:Russian communists]]\n[[Category:Russian powerlifters]]\n[[Category:Russian strength athletes]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{Expand Russian|topic=bio|\u041d\u0430\u0443\u043c\u043e\u0432\u0430, \u041c\u0430\u0440\u044c\u044f\u043d\u0430 \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0430|date=November 2014}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Maryana Naumova\n| image       = \u041d\u0430\u0443\u043c\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u041c\u0430\u0440\u044c\u044f\u043d\u0430, \u043d\u0430\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043d\u0430 \u0442\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0438\u0440\u0435 \u0410\u0440\u043d\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0434 \u041a\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0441\u0438\u043a.jpg\n| image_size  =\n| caption     =  Naumova at the 2013 [[Arnold Classic]]\n| other_names = \n| birth_name  = Maryana Aleksandrovna Naumova\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1999|4|22|}}\n| death_date  = \n| residence   = \n| nationality = [[Russian people|Russian]]\n| known_for   = \n| employer    = \n| occupation  = \n| height      = \n| weight      = \n}}\n'''Maryana Aleksandrovna Naumova''' ({{lang-ru|\u041c\u0430\u0440\u0438\u0430\u0301\u043d\u0430 \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u0301\u043d\u0434\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0430 \u041d\u0430\u0443\u0301\u043c\u043e\u0432\u0430}}; born 22 April 1999 in [[Staraya Russa]]) is a [[Russia]]n [[powerlifting|powerlifter]], who specializes in [[bench press]], and is the leading teenage girl in the world in the discipline. She has won multiple world championships, has set over 15 world records<!-- in the bench press--> in her age category and holds the title of [[Master of Sport of Russia|Master of Sport of Russia, International Class]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://mstrok.ru/?id=1947|script-title=ru:\u0421\u0430\u043c\u0430\u044f \u0441\u0438\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0434\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0447\u043a\u0430 \u043f\u043b\u0430\u043d\u0435\u0442\u044b \u043f\u043e\u0441\u0435\u0442\u0438\u043b\u0430 \u041d\u0438\u0436\u043d\u0438\u0439 \u0422\u0430\u0433\u0438\u043b|publisher=News agency \"Mezhdu Strok\"|date=2013-11-05|language=Russian|accessdate=2014-10-23}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nMaryana Naumova is the first female under-18 to be allowed to participate in professional powerlifting tournaments.<ref name=\"aif.ru 2015-03-09\" /> In March 2015 she participated in the [[Arnold Classic]], establishing the female record in the event Arnold BenchBach, lifting 150&nbsp;kg (331&nbsp;lbs). After the tournament she asked [[Arnold Schwarzenegger]] to become the [[President of the United States]] and normalize [[Russia\u2013United States relations]]. She also passed Arnold letters from [[Donbass]] children.<ref name=\"aif.ru 2015-03-09\">{{cite news|title=\u0428\u043a\u043e\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0430 \u0438\u0437 \u041f\u043e\u0434\u043c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u044c\u044f \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0430\u043b\u0430 \u0428\u0432\u0430\u0440\u0446\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0433\u0433\u0435\u0440\u0443 \u043f\u0438\u0441\u044c\u043c\u0430 \u043e\u0442 \u0434\u0435\u0442\u0435\u0439 \u0414\u043e\u043d\u0431\u0430\u0441\u0441\u0430|url=http://www.aif.ru/sport/other/1462834|agency=[[Argumenty i Fakty]]|date=9 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=\u0421\u0430\u043c\u0430\u044f \u0441\u0438\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0434\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0447\u043a\u0430 \u0432 \u043c\u0438\u0440\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0438\u043b\u0430 \u0428\u0432\u0430\u0440\u0446\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0433\u0433\u0435\u0440\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u043c\u0438\u0440\u0438\u0442\u044c \u0421\u0428\u0410 \u0438 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u044e|url=http://lenta.ru/news/2015/03/09/naumova/|agency=[[Lenta.ru|Lenta]]|date=9 March 2015}}</ref>\n\nAs part of [[Russia's role in the Syrian Civil War|Russia's support]] for the Assad government during the [[Syrian Civil War]], Naumova was sent to Damascus at the invitation of [[Asma al-Assad]], the president\u2019s wife.<ref>{{cite news|title=Syria: Positions harden|url=https://www.economist.com/news/middle-east-and-africa/21664155-hopes-diplomatic-progress-aimed-ending-war-go-reverse-positions|accessdate=12 September 2015|work=[[The Economist]]|date=12 September 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn commemoration of the late Russian revolutionary [[Vladimir Lenin]], Naumova had joined the [[Communist Party of the Russian Federation]] to celebrate Lenin's 146th birthday and lay flowers at the Mausoleum on Red Square. Naumova was awarded the Order of the UCP-CPSU - also known as \"Friendship of the People\" - for her humanitarian aid work throughout the world. Professional MMA fighter [[Jeff Monson]] had also joined Naumova and the Communist Party to celebrate the life and legacy of Lenin.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u0413.\u0410. \u0417\u044e\u0433\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432: \u041d\u0430 \u043f\u043b\u0430\u043d\u0435\u0442\u0435 \u043d\u0435\u043c\u0430\u043b\u043e \u0438\u0437\u0432\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043b\u044e\u0434\u0435\u0439, \u043d\u043e \u043d\u0435\u043c\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0433\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435\u0432|url=https://kprf.ru/party-live/cknews/154216.html|work=KPRF|date=22 April 2016|language=Russian}}</ref>\n\nAt the 2016 Arnolds Sports Festival she participated in the SSP Nutrition Pro Raw Bench competition. She lifted 110&nbsp;kg and placed 3rd, but was later disqualified due to a positive doping test and suspended from lifting for two years.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.powerlifting-ipf.com/fileadmin/ipf/data/anti-doping/IPF_current_ADRV-list_2016_06_16.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-08-03 |url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160917053950/http://www.powerlifting-ipf.com/fileadmin/ipf/data/anti-doping/IPF_current_ADRV-list_2016_06_16.pdf |archivedate=2016-09-17 |df= }}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n===Inline citations===\n{{reflist}}\n\n===General references===\n: <small>{{cite news|url=http://ria.ru/video/20100315/214343203.html|script-title=ru:\u0414\u0435\u0441\u044f\u0442\u0438\u043b\u0435\u0442\u043d\u044f\u044f \u0434\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0447\u043a\u0430 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0442 \u0440\u0435\u043a\u043e\u0440\u0434\u044b |publisher=[[RIA Novosti]]|date=2010-03-15|language=Russian|accessdate=2014-10-23}}<br />{{cite news|url=http://rt.com/sport/powerlifting-maryana-naumova-guinness-record-765-881/|title=Girl raises bar on Guinness powerlifting record|publisher=[[Russia Today]]|date=2011-09-06|accessdate=2014-10-23}}<br />{{cite news|url=http://en.ria.ru/video/20110929/167248224.html|title=Russia\u2019s strongest girl yells at barbell to win|publisher=[[RIA Novosti]]|date=2011-09-29|language=Russian|accessdate=2014-10-23}}<br />{{cite news|url=http://en.ria.ru/video/20111117/168777676.html|title=Russian schoolgirl breaks world powerlifting record|publisher=[[